Description: Fix Make.rules dep declaration for %-blacklist.esl rule

The %-blacklist.esl rule's recipe invokes ./cert-to-efi-sig-list, but the
declared dependency list names cert-to-efi-hash-list (a different binary).
Under parallel make, this lets the rule fire before cert-to-efi-sig-list
is fully linked — exec() on a half-written ELF returns EACCES, which make
reports as "Permission denied" / Error 127.

Fix: declare cert-to-efi-sig-list as the dep, matching the recipe.
Mirrors the %.esl rule's correct dep declaration two lines below.

Surfaced by InterGenOS Build #7 phase_core_extra at efitools (2026-05-10):
  ./cert-to-efi-sig-list PK.crt PK-blacklist.esl
  make: ./cert-to-efi-sig-list: Permission denied
  make: *** [Make.rules:75: PK-blacklist.esl] Error 127

Author: InterGenJLU <InterGenJLU@users.noreply.github.com>
Last-Update: 2026-05-10

--- efitools-1.9.2.orig/Make.rules
+++ efitools-1.9.2/Make.rules
@@ -71,7 +71,7 @@
 %.hash: %.efi hash-to-efi-sig-list
 	./hash-to-efi-sig-list $< $@

-%-blacklist.esl: %.crt cert-to-efi-hash-list
+%-blacklist.esl: %.crt cert-to-efi-sig-list
 	./cert-to-efi-sig-list $< $@

 %-hash-blacklist.esl: %.crt cert-to-efi-hash-list
